of The Vagrants on the Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edano</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#333333>(5/25/01 12:31:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hit 44 last night... now what?</span><hr size=1> SolB is good at 44.  You can really contribute to a group at most of the camp spots:  window (great exp, no loot to speak of), named (lots of named kobolds and the potential for nice loot) or BnB (Bugs N Bats - has some really nice rare drops).<br>
<br>
I got a 10 slot, 100% weight reducing bag for small items only in BnB yesterday.  The action is fast and occasionally frantic, but with a good group you can make fast exp and have fun.<br>
<br>
If you want a break from grouping, you can now solo HGs in Rathe mountains with relative ease.  This is the method I use:<br>
<br>
1) Summon, SoW and burnout pet (I use fire because I don't have any others :(<br>
2) Get a SoW or click on that potion or Jboots.<br>
3) Pull a HG with Elemental Maelstorm (low agro with decent damage).<br>
4) Sic on pet and run until he's taunted on to the pet<br>
5) Cast Shock of Swords and the giant will run after you again.<br>
6) Wait until DoT wears off, he will be down to a slither of health.  Allow pet to melee him to death or just finish with blaze.<br>
<br>
You can do this but a little better if you partner with a low level druid.  At level 45 I still shared exp with a level 30.  Get him to use track and pull with snare.  Turn pet taunt off and cast the two spells listed above.  Put on pet and within 40 seconds the giant will be dead.  The DoT will work him to death while the pet gets free hits at the giant's rear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nickoteen>Nickoteen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#333333>(5/25/01 6:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hit 44 last night... now what?</span><hr size=1> every single place mentioned was horrible xp, camp the arena guards in freeport. amazing xp and fast spawn, best I have ever in my entire game experience seen <p><img src="http://website.lineone.net/~rexz/nomsig.jpg" width="400" height="160">[AHREF.="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=74151"]

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uscrubfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scrubfire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#333333>(5/25/01 7:01:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   SolB and Guk</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the suggestions.  I think I've found where I'm going to park for a while... SolB.  I can easily split a 2 kobold spawn using my fire pet (wish I had my earth pet... it would be easier) and solo at the zone line.<br>
<br>
I tried the northernmost zone from SolA last night.  Hopefully I can get into some pickup groups.  I can also pop over to SolA every once and a while and kill the blazing elementals hoping to get the power of fire.<br>
<br>
On another note, I spent 7 frustrating hours in LGuk last night.  I can't complain to much because I got 3 bubbles of exp, but the only way I got that exp was to tag along with 55+ level solo/duo campers.  I was flattered by the invites and did my best to help out with Damage shielding and mod rodding (I can see how quick that will stop being fun), but I was left yelling for a group as soon as they decided to leave.  If I had been in a full group around my level at least we could have held the spot and called for a replacement.<br>
<br>
One last question.  Does anyone know the spawn time in SolB?  It's vital information if you are soloing. <p>--------------------------<BR>
Kennethjames Scrubfire<BR>
Mage of the 44th 
Summoning, Mithaniel Marr<BR>
Member of the guild Dragon Maw<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukithary.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kithary</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(5/25/01 11:09:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research on Mithaniel Marr</span><hr size=1> Kennethjames, I am maxed at research.  Send me a tell and we'll see about getting you set up with the rest of your 44th and 49th level spells.<br>
<br>
 <p><i><font color=red>Kithary Tir`Brethil</i></font><br>
55th Conjurer of Mithaniel Marr<br>
Adamantine Kinship</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=arlannaamanodel>ArlannaAmanodel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(6/6/02 6:49:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research on Mithaniel Marr</span><hr size=1> At 44 I went to Katta and bought my lvl 44 pets. Then figured since I was already on the moon I would go to echo. A guildie of mine suggested it and I can tell you it is awesome exp. 1 kill nets me about half a blue bub of exp. When you zone in from the short quarter in SH go past the haven defender you see...there are 4 under bulks here. Kill em. They will net you about 2 blues of exp. They have a long respawn time so don't try and camp them. After you kill all 4, continue on the path and take your first right. Set up cam here. You will try to break the spawn in the room to your left. Once it is done go and sit in the room and you will be set. Just look out for fireclaw here. He hits hard when you're only 44. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#333333>(6/7/02 7:40:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research on Mithaniel Marr</span><hr size=1> Yeah, the problem with echo and those Underbulks (at least on my server) is that usually too many people try to kill them ;-) and since the cave is small, the respawn time is long, there's not enough for everybody once there are 2 groups/people hunting them ;-) <p><img SRC="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_zdd2.jpg"> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uyomad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>YoMaD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#333333>(6/10/02 1:03:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research on Mithaniel Marr</span><hr size=1> Yep, just head for Echo. It's the best exp you can get at 44. If you can get a C3 from Bazaar or Shadowhaven that would help a lot. Fireclaw is L. 40 and hits for 110 I think. You can easily solo him with earth at fm. I got him down to 10% with 2 bubs of mana and then I just ran because pet died. The stonegrabbers there also drop around 13pp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#333333>(6/11/02 9:18:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels4950.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=127.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   L44-45/46</span><hr size=1> well I levelled from 42 to 44 in almost no time in Dawnshroud.<br>
I decided to stay at 44 there and with the new pets I flew through that level again there (far less than 1 hour per yellow bubble).<br>
At 45 about 50% of the Large Zelniaks were lightblue, but still...1 hour per yellow bubble at that lvl.<br>
<br>
Yesterday I did hit lvl 46 and thought that I finally had to move away.<br>
But now...still about 25% of the Large Zelniaks are darkblue, as well as about 50% of the normal Wolfs (and of course all the special critters). for instance a Blood starved Wolf (if you know where you can force them to spawn, they have proximity traps as spawn triggers) still gives almost half a blue per kill.<br>
<br>
I could only stay 30 minutes after I hit 46, but still I got slightly above 2 blues in that time (makes a bit above 6 hours per lvl, which I think isnt all that bad at 46).<br>
<br>
If you know where to hunt (dont stay at the entrance where everybody hunts ;-) ), your firepet will eat those critters and except for Wolfs you hardly ever have to Nuke heavily (beside the lvl 8 Bolt spell for pulling ;-) ).<br>
<br>
You don't get much xp per MOB anymore, but you can kill non-stop and the risk is zero for you (never ever died since I went there at 42).<br>
And you won't have to look for MOBs, there will always be plenty around you (again, if you find some nice spot).<br>
So even I didn't think I would still be there at 46, I think now I will. I simply don't know any other place where I can get through lvl 46 in about 6 hours with practically zero risk.<br>
<br>
In comparision Echo Caverns:<br>
- at least on my server often many people in there.<br>
- pretty tough MOBs, might be hard to get away if you get aggro (now that you wont be able to train adds on pet always anymore)<br>
- BUT, if you could always kill as many as you can handle, you probably would get through lvl 46 faster than in DP ;-)<br>
